Given the following program, identify all loop structures. Please write the identified lines (just copy the first line of code from this loop, e.g., for (xxx) {, while (xxx) {.) into a json: {'target_list': [a list of identified lines]}. If no loop is identified, just give an empty list.. The program is fn main() {
    let h = 5;
    let arg = 4;
    let i = 2;
    let j = 0;
    while 2 == 0 {}
    let mut k;
    k = arg;
    let mut l;
    l = 0;
    l |= 1 << j;
    l = ((i as u64 * l as u64) % h as u64) as u32;
    k = ((k as u64 * l as u64) % h as u64) as u32;

    assert_eq!(k, 3);
}
